# Review Policy

Reviews must be structured findings, not impressions.

## Required dimensions

- Correctness: logic, edge cases, concurrency, null/none, state transitions, data loss.
- Test coverage: acceptance criteria, negative cases, RED/GREEN evidence, determinism.
- Architecture: boundaries, layering, API contracts, dependency direction, scope fit.
- Quality: naming, readability, duplication, complexity, maintainability.
- Security/privacy: secrets, injection, authz/authn, sensitive data, unsafe dependencies.
- Operability: observability, retries, failure modes, configuration, deployment impact.
- Domain: only when a project pack is active.

## Finding format

Every finding must include severity, location, violated requirement/invariant, problem, evidence, required outcome, and suggested regression test where applicable.

## Gate rule

Any BLOCKER finding fails the review gate. MAJOR findings require repair or explicit human acceptance. MINOR/NIT findings must not trigger broad unrelated refactors.
